The Fukuchiyama Moto-Ise complex is a Shrine complex consisting of three different shrines. Two of them are [[Moto-Ise Shrines]] for {{ill|Kōtai Jingū|ja|皇大神宮|1=Kōtai Jingū|2=ja|3=皇大神宮|4=zh|5=皇大神宮|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Toyouke Daijingu|ja|豊受大神宮|1=Toyouke Daijingu|2=ja|3=豊受大神宮|4=zh|5=豐受大神宮|12=draft|12=draft}} respectively and one is a core cave. Possibly the amanoiwato shrine but I am not sure. == Overview == The shrine is one of the {{ill|Moto-Ise Shrines|ja|元伊勢|1=Moto-Ise Shrines|12=draft|12=draft}} located in the Ōe area of the city (details at '''{{ill|Kotai Shrine|ja|皇大神社 (福知山市)|12=draft|12=draft}}'''). Amanoiwato Shrine is considered the inner shrine of Kōtai Jingu Shrine.
